g.title: COMMENT_7bb42c0+1
g.text: !> brief Perform multiple pressure solves until velocity tolerance is satisfied

g.title: COMMENT_7bb67a0+1
g.text: Here we need an exchange of F for linking:

g.title: COMMENT_7b93280+1
g.text: The following loops and exchange always get executed the first pass through the PRESSURE_ITERATION_LOOP.
If we need to iterate the baroclinic torque term, the loop is executed each time.

g.title: COMMENT_7bbe0a0+1
g.text: Compute the right hand side (RHS) and boundary conditions for the Poission equation for pressure.
The WALL_WORK1 array is computed in COMPUTE_VELOCITY_ERROR, but it should
be zero the first time the pressure solver is called.

g.title: COMMENT_7bc2640+1
g.text: Special case for tunnels -- filter out the lengthwise pressure gradient

g.title: COMMENT_7bc1dc0+1
g.text: Solve the Poission equation using either FFT or ULMAT, GLMAT, or UGLMAT

g.title: COMMENT_7bc78c0+1
g.text: Check the residuals of the Poisson solution

g.title: COMMENT_7bc97a0+1
g.text: Exchange both H or HS and FVX, FVY, FVZ and then estimate values of U, V, W (US, VS, WS) at next time step.

g.title: COMMENT_7bc8500+1
g.text: Make all MPI processes aware of the maximum velocity error to decide if another pressure iteration is needed.

g.title: COMMENT_7be5280+1
g.text: If the VELOCITY_TOLERANCE is satisfied or max/min iterations are hit, exit the loop.

g.title: COMMENT_7befea0+1
g.text: Exit the iteration loop if satisfactory progress is not achieved
